Constable Mziwonke Siwisa was gunned down outside his home in Kraaifontein last week. CAPE TOWN - The case against three men accused of killing a Cape Town police officer has been postponed to later this week.Constable Mziwonke Siwisa was gunned down outside his home in Kraaifontein last week. The 35-year-old from the Sea Border Unit at Table Bay Harbour was waiting for transport to report for duty. The men accused of the murder have opted to apply for legal aid.The trio, in their early 20s, were arrested during a joint operation between the Hawks and the SAPS in Bloekombos in Kraaifontein last week.It s believed Siwisa was targeted for his service pistol.The State will also use this time to compile and complete full bail profiles for the accused.They re due back in the dock on Wednesday.